PN,37502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773155489
OL,3,CPolice officer denies dismissing
OL,4,Cassault complaint about Nottingham
OL,5,Ckiller
OL,7,FThe inquiry, taking place in central
OL,8,FLondon, has previously heard how
OL,9,FCalocane headbutted, punched and swung
OL,10,Fhandcuffs at a police officer on
OL,11,FSeptember 3 2021.
OL,13,FCalocane went on to fatally stab
OL,14,FUniversity of Nottingham
OL,15,Fundergraduates Barnaby Webber and
OL,16,FGrace O'Malley-Kumar, both 19, and
OL,17,Fgrandfather Ian Coates, 65, and
OL,18,Fattempted to kill three more people in
OL,19,Fthe early hours of June 13 2023.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773155489
OL,3,CPolice officer denies dismissing
OL,4,Cassault complaint about Nottingham
OL,5,Ckiller
OL,7,FGiving evidence on Monday, Pc Zacharia
OL,8,Fdenied that Christopher showed him a
OL,9,Fvideo of him being held in a headlock,
OL,10,Fand denied telling him at the scene:
OL,11,F"Well, you don't have any injuries do
OL,12,Fyou?" and "Well, we don't have enough
OL,13,Ffor ABH (assault occasioning actual
OL,14,Fbodily harm)".
OL,16,FTold that Christopher's evidence to
OL,17,Fthe inquiry was that the officer had
OL,18,Fbeen very dismissive of his assault
OL,19,Fcomplaint, Pc Zacharia said: "That's
OL,20,Fabsolutely not true.
OL,26,@sD@AOUtD@EO]tD@KOUvD@MO]{D@^OU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773155489
OL,3,CPolice officer denies dismissing
OL,4,Cassault complaint about Nottingham
OL,5,Ckiller
OL,7,F"When I go for a job I give it 100%.
OL,9,F"They have called us for a reason. I
OL,10,Fwould never be dismissive or dismiss
OL,11,Fanyone. Crime is crime.
OL,13,F"Whether he was injured or not if he
OL,14,Fhad been willing to make a statement I
OL,15,Fwould have investigated it to the
OL,16,Ffullest."
OL,18,FPc Zacharia and his colleague Sergeant
OL,19,FFaulkner, who also attended the scene,
OL,20,Fdid not arrest Calocane.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@AOUuD@AOUxD@IO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773155489
OL,3,CPolice officer denies dismissing
OL,4,Cassault complaint about Nottingham
OL,5,Ckiller
OL,7,F"At that time the situation was all
OL,8,Fcalmed down," the police constable
OL,9,Ftold the inquiry.
OL,11,F"In speaking with Sergeant Faulkner
OL,12,F(Calocane) was calm, he was compliant,
OL,13,Fand I've got Christopher who is not
OL,14,Fwanting to make a complaint and not
OL,15,Fengaging very well, so we felt that
OL,16,Fthings had calmed down and it wasn't
OL,17,Fnecessary or proportionate to be
OL,18,Farresting him at that time."
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@MO]sD@AOUzD@\O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773155489
OL,3,CPolice officer denies dismissing
OL,4,Cassault complaint about Nottingham
OL,5,Ckiller
OL,7,FAsked if he took matters at face value
OL,8,Fwithout making obvious checks, the
OL,9,Fofficer said: "We can only go on what
OL,10,Fis presented to us when we attend any
OL,11,Fjob."
OL,13,FHe was asked multiple times on Monday
OL,14,Fwhether he made checks on police
OL,15,Fsystems to gather more information
OL,16,Fabout Calocane, including any history
OL,17,Fof offending, but said he cannot
OL,18,Fremember.
OL,26,@qD@OOUsD@EO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773155489
OL,3,CPolice officer denies dismissing
OL,4,Cassault complaint about Nottingham
OL,5,Ckiller
OL,7,FOn the suggestion that Christopher was
OL,8,Fcoached by him when the student gave a
OL,9,Fstatement the next day declaring he
OL,10,Fdid not want to pursue the complaint,
OL,11,FPc Zacharia said: "Absolutely not true.
OL,13,F"When we do write out these pocket
OL,14,Fnotebook entries they have an
OL,15,Fopportunity to read it, to amend it,
OL,16,Fto say they don't like something and I
OL,17,Fwould have gotten him also to have
OL,18,Fread that as well so that is
OL,19,Fabsolutely not true."
OL,26,@sD@SOUuD@AOU{D@UO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
